@startuml
!include theme.iuml
title Logical Component Diagram — Decoupled Bounded Contexts
left to right direction
package "Clients" {
  [React Web] as Web
  [Future Mobile Client] as Mobile
  [Organizer Console] as Console
}
[API Gateway] as Gateway
[Identity & Access] as Identity
[Catalog & Discovery] as Catalog
[Reservation & Inventory] as Reservation
[Virtual Waiting Room] as Waiting
[Billing & Checkout] as Billing
[Ticket Verification] as Tickets
[Notification Worker] as Notification
[Analytics Projection] as Analytics
database "PostgreSQL\n(system of record)" as PostgreSQL
collections "Redis\nlocks, queue counters, cache" as Redis
queue "RabbitMQ\nintegration events" as RabbitMQ
cloud "External Payment Gateway" as PaymentGateway
cloud "Email / SMS Providers" as Providers
Web --> Gateway : HTTPS / WebSocket
Mobile ..> Gateway : future HTTPS
Console --> Gateway : HTTPS
Gateway --> Identity : authenticate / authorize
Gateway --> Catalog : queries and administration
Gateway --> Waiting : admission
Gateway --> Reservation : commands / inventory
Gateway --> Billing : checkout
Gateway --> Tickets : QR verification
Identity --> PostgreSQL
Catalog --> PostgreSQL
Reservation --> PostgreSQL : durable reservation
Reservation --> Redis : atomic TTL locks
Waiting --> Redis : ordered admission
Waiting --> PostgreSQL : auditable entries
Billing --> PostgreSQL : payment saga + tickets
Billing --> PaymentGateway
Billing --> RabbitMQ : payment.* / ticket.*
Reservation --> RabbitMQ : reservation.*
RabbitMQ --> Notification
RabbitMQ --> Analytics
Notification --> PostgreSQL : delivery log / inbox
Notification --> Providers
Analytics --> PostgreSQL : read model
note bottom of Gateway
  Unified edge: TLS termination, JWT validation,
  correlation IDs, throttling and route policy.
end note
@enduml
